--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Project description:
This is a system is designed to help students manage their academic tasks, track their study habits, and improve productivity in a simple 
and effective way. It integrates task management, mood tracking, and study time analysis into one platform to support better study planning.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

File structure:
.
├── app.py                        # Flask application & API routes
├── requirements.txt              # Python dependencies
├── nmlm_users.db                 # SQLite database (users & tasks)
│
├── index.html                    # Main single-page app (dashboard,auth, tasks, etc.)
├── otp.html                      # Email OTP verification page
│
├── css/
│   ├── style.css                 # Main stylesheet
│   ├── modals.css                # Modal-specific styles
│   └── zen.css                   # Zen Mode styles
│
├── js/
│   ├── main.js                   # Core app logic (calendar, tasks, pomodoro, mood themes)
│   ├── app-init.js               # Post-login data bootstrapping (user info, stats, tasks)
│   ├── api.js                    # API client wrapper (fetch helpers, endpoints)
│   ├── api-service.js            # Alternate/legacy API client wrapper
│   ├── render-engine.js          # DOM rendering for tasks, leaderboard, user info
│   └── particle.js               # Zen Mode particle/audio visualization engine
│
├──assets/
├── img/
│   └── NMLM_logo.png             # App logo
└── audio/
│   ├── alarm/
│   │   └── alarm.mpeg            # Pomodoro end-of-session alarm sound
│   └── pomodoro/
│         ├── audio_01.mpeg       # Zen Mode ambient audio tracks
│         ├── audio_02.mpeg
│         ├── audio_03.mpeg
│         ├── audio_04.mpeg
│         ├── audio_05.mpeg
│         └── audio_06.mpeg
│ 
├── venv/                        # Local Python virtual environment (not committed)
└── .git/                        # Git repository metadata


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

How to view the website:
1. Download the zip file and extract it.
2. Open a terminal in that folder and run: code . (This opens the extracted folder directly in Visual Studio Code)
3. Terminal > New Terminal > python -m venv venv > enter > pip install flask flask-sqlalchemy pyjwt werkzeug flask-cors flask-mail > enter > python app.py > enter
4. Open the frontend with Live Server
3. Navigate using the navigation bar or in-page buttons to move between the different sections of the website.

